&lt;p&gt;The summary of this page ends here.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Mathematical Typesetting Test</title><link>https://hugo-classless.netlify.app/posts/math-test/</link><pubDate>Wed, 15 Feb 2023 10:00:00 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://hugo-classless.netlify.app/posts/math-test/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This page tests the mathematical typesetting capabilities of the site, which are powered by KaTeX.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; For this to render correctly, KaTeX support must be enabled in your site&amp;rsquo;s configuration. See the Hugo documentation for details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id="inline-formulas"&gt;Inline Formulas&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mathematical formulas can be included directly in a sentence. For example, the famous Pythagorean theorem is written as \( a^2 + b^2 = c^2 \). Another common inline formula is Euler&amp;rsquo;s identity, \( e^{i\pi} + 1 = 0 \), which beautifully connects five fundamental mathematical constants.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Diagram Testing</title><link>https://hugo-classless.netlify.app/posts/diagram/</link><pubDate>Wed, 15 Feb 2023 09:00:00 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://hugo-classless.netlify.app/posts/diagram/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="hey"&gt;Hey&lt;/h1&gt;
